// Expected Output Order:
// Start
// Middle
// Sync Function
// End
// Promise 1
// Promise 2
// Timeout 1 (0ms)
// Timeout 2 (10ms)

// Step-by-step Explanation:

// 1. Initial Synchronous Execution:
//    - `console.log('Start');` -> Logs 'Start'. Call Stack: [console.log]
//    - `setTimeout(() => { console.log('Timeout 1 (0ms)'); }, 0);` -> Timer starts, callback moves to Web API, then to Callback (Macrotask) Queue when 0ms expires. Call Stack: []
//    - `Promise.resolve().then(() => { console.log('Promise 1'); });` -> Promise resolves immediately, callback moves to Microtask Queue. Call Stack: []
//    - `console.log('Middle');` -> Logs 'Middle'. Call Stack: [console.log]
//    - `setTimeout(() => { console.log('Timeout 2 (10ms)'); }, 10);` -> Timer starts, callback moves to Web API, then to Callback (Macrotask) Queue after 10ms. Call Stack: []
//    - `Promise.resolve().then(() => { console.log('Promise 2'); });` -> Promise resolves immediately, callback moves to Microtask Queue. Call Stack: []
//    - `syncFunction();` -> `console.log('Sync Function');` -> Logs 'Sync Function'. Call Stack: [syncFunction, console.log]
//    - `console.log('End');` -> Logs 'End'. Call Stack: [console.log]
//    At this point, all synchronous code is done. Call Stack is empty.

// Current state of queues (conceptual):
// Microtask Queue: [() => { console.log('Promise 1'); }, () => { console.log('Promise 2'); }]
// Callback Queue:  [() => { console.log('Timeout 1 (0ms)'); }, () => { console.log('Timeout 2 (10ms)'); }]

// 2. Event Loop Cycle Begins (Call Stack is empty):
//    - Event Loop checks Microtask Queue first.
//    - Dequeues `Promise 1` callback and pushes to Call Stack.
//    - `console.log('Promise 1');` -> Logs 'Promise 1'. Call Stack: [console.log]
//    - Call Stack becomes empty.
//    - Event Loop checks Microtask Queue again (it processes *all* microtasks before checking macrotasks).
//    - Dequeues `Promise 2` callback and pushes to Call Stack.
//    - `console.log('Promise 2');` -> Logs 'Promise 2'. Call Stack: [console.log]
//    - Call Stack becomes empty. Microtask Queue is now empty.

// 3. Event Loop Processes Callback (Macrotask) Queue:
//    - Event Loop checks Callback Queue.
//    - Dequeues `Timeout 1 (0ms)` callback and pushes to Call Stack.
//    - `console.log('Timeout 1 (0ms)');` -> Logs 'Timeout 1 (0ms)'. Call Stack: [console.log]
//    - Call Stack becomes empty.
//    - Event Loop checks Microtask Queue (still empty).
//    - Event Loop checks Callback Queue.
//    - Dequeues `Timeout 2 (10ms)` callback and pushes to Call Stack (assuming 10ms has passed).
//    - `console.log('Timeout 2 (10ms)');` -> Logs 'Timeout 2 (10ms)'. Call Stack: [console.log]
//    - Call Stack becomes empty. Callback Queue is now empty.

// The Event Loop continues to run, but all queues are empty.
